    If (((NUM WHITE PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) + NUM WHITE PAWNS (EVAL)) == 0) And (PIECE EVAL (NO PAWNS) < -450))
    {
        evaluation res (WD) += -4000;
        possible to win finished (eval) = 1;
        Stop(this script);
    }
    If (((NUM BLACK PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) + NUM BLACK PAWNS (EVAL)) == 0) And (PIECE EVAL (NO PAWNS) > 450))
    {
        evaluation res (WD) += 4000;
        possible to win finished (eval) = 1;
        Stop(this script);
    }
}

Define draw_tweaks.init (warp=true)
{
    draw tweaks delta eval = 0;
    draw tweaks win correction delta = 0;
    possible to win finished (eval) = 0;
    kings in opposition res (eval) = (1 * (((WhiteKingFile (eval) == BlackKingFile (eval)) And (abs((WhiteKingRank (eval) - BlackKingRank (eval))) == 2)) Or ((WhiteKingRank (eval) == BlackKingRank (eval)) And (abs((WhiteKingFile (eval) - BlackKingFile (eval))) == 2))));
    delta passers (poss. to win) = (num white passers (eval) - num black passers (eval));
    draw tweaks black drawn = 0;
    draw tweaks white drawn = 0;
}

Define draw_tweaks.king_closer_wrapper(string target square)(bool white?) (warp=true)
{
    Call is_x_closer_y(blackKingID(eval))(whiteKingID(eval))(target square);
    If (is x closer than y to square res == 1)
    {
        If white?
        {
            draw tweaks delta eval += -999;
            draw tweaks white drawn = 1;
        }
        Else
        {
            draw tweaks delta eval += 999;
            draw tweaks black drawn = 1;
        }
    }
}

Define draw_tweaks.majors_ending(string draw eval) (warp=true)
{
    If (abs(PIECE EVAL (NO PAWNS)) < 50)
    {
        Call // comment("small material imbalance (if any)");
        If ((NUM BLACK MAJOR PIECES (EVAL) > 0) And ((NUM BLACK MAJOR PIECES (EVAL) + NUM WHITE MAJOR PIECES (EVAL)) == (NUM BLACK PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) + NUM WHITE PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL))))
        {
            Call // comment("only major pieces");
            If (abs((NUM WHITE PAWNS (EVAL) - NUM BLACK PAWNS (EVAL))) < 2)
            {
                Call // comment("small pawn imbalance (if any)");
                If ((num black passers (eval) + num white passers (eval)) == 0)
                {
                    Call draw_tweaks.change_delta_eval(-150) stm relative((evaluation res (WD) > draw eval));
                }
            }
            Call // comment("special major endgame scaling");
            Call draw_tweaks.special_rook | our pawns:(NUM WHITE PAWNS (EVAL)) their pawns:(NUM BLACK PAWNS (EVAL)) their most advanced pawn rank:(most advanced black pawn rank (eval)) our king rank:(WhiteKingRank (eval)) their king rank:(BlackKingRank (eval)) their most advanced pawn file:(most advanced black pawn file (eval)) our king file:(WhiteKingFile (eval)) our most advanced pawn rank:(most advanced white pawn rank (eval)) our passers:(num white passers (eval)) their passers:(num black passers (eval)) their king file:(BlackKingFile (eval))((1 == 1));
            Call draw_tweaks.special_rook | our pawns:(NUM BLACK PAWNS (EVAL)) their pawns:(NUM WHITE PAWNS (EVAL)) their most advanced pawn rank:((9 - most advanced white pawn rank (eval))) our king rank:((9 - BlackKingRank (eval))) their king rank:((9 - WhiteKingRank (eval))) their most advanced pawn file:(most advanced white pawn file (eval)) our king file:(BlackKingFile (eval)) our most advanced pawn rank:((9 - most advanced black pawn rank (eval))) our passers:(num black passers (eval)) their passers:(num white passers (eval)) their king file:(WhiteKingFile (eval))((0 == 1));
        }
    }
}

Define draw_tweaks.minor_or_exchange_up (warp=true)
{
    If ((NUM BLACK PAWNS (EVAL) + NUM WHITE PAWNS (EVAL)) == 0)
    {
        Call // comment("no pawns");
        If (PIECE EVAL (NO PAWNS) < 0)
        {
            Call // comment("black has more material");
            If ((kings in opposition res (eval) == 1) And (WD_distance_to_closest_edge[whiteKingID(eval)] == 0))
            {
                draw tweaks delta eval += -100;
            }
            If ((NUM BLACK PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) == NUM WHITE PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL)) And (PIECE EVAL (NO PAWNS) > -200))
            {
                Call // comment("Exchange Up");
                draw tweaks delta eval += 325;
                Stop(this script);
            }
            If (((NUM BLACK PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) - 1) == NUM WHITE PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL)) And (PIECE EVAL (NO PAWNS) > -350))
            {
                Call // comment("Minor Piece Up");
                draw tweaks delta eval += 525;
                Stop(this script);
            }
        }
        If (PIECE EVAL (NO PAWNS) > 0)
        {
            Call // comment("white has more material");
            If ((kings in opposition res (eval) == 1) And (WD_distance_to_closest_edge[blackKingID(eval)] == 0))
            {
                draw tweaks delta eval += 100;
            }
            If ((NUM WHITE PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) == NUM BLACK PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL)) And (PIECE EVAL (NO PAWNS) < 200))
            {
                Call // comment("Exchange Up");
                draw tweaks delta eval += -325;
                Stop(this script);
            }
            If (((NUM WHITE PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) - 1) == NUM BLACK PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL)) And (PIECE EVAL (NO PAWNS) < 350))
            {
                Call // comment("Minor Piece Up");
                draw tweaks delta eval += -525;
                Stop(this script);
            }
        }
    }
}

Define draw_tweaks.one_side_drawn(bool white?)(string draw eval) (warp=true)
{
    If white?
    {
        Call // comment("white");
        If (evaluation res (WD) > draw eval)
        {
            If ((NUM WHITE MAJOR PIECES (EVAL) == 0) And ((NUM WHITE MINOR PIECES (EVAL) < 2) And (NUM WHITE PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) < 2)))
            {
                Call // comment("white has <= one minor piece");
                If (NUM WHITE PAWNS (EVAL) == 0)
                {
                    draw tweaks delta eval += -999;
                    draw tweaks white drawn = 1;
                }
                If (NUM WHITE PAWNS (EVAL) == 1)
                {
                    Call draw_tweaks.outside_pawn(8)(most advanced white pawn file (eval))(8)(((NUM WHITE PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) == 0) Or ((NUM WHITE BISHOPS (EVAL) == 1) And (WHITE BISHOP TYPE (EVAL) == "light"))))((1 == 1));
                    Call draw_tweaks.outside_pawn(1)(most advanced white pawn file (eval))(1)(((NUM WHITE PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) == 0) Or ((NUM WHITE BISHOPS (EVAL) == 1) And (WHITE BISHOP TYPE (EVAL) == "dark"))))((1 == 1));
                }
            }
            Stop(this script);
        }
    }
    Else
    {
        Call // comment("black");
        If (evaluation res (WD) < draw eval)
        {
            If ((NUM BLACK MAJOR PIECES (EVAL) == 0) And ((NUM BLACK MINOR PIECES (EVAL) < 2) And (NUM BLACK PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) < 2)))
            {
                Call // comment("black has <= one minor piece");
                If (NUM BLACK PAWNS (EVAL) == 0)
                {
                    draw tweaks delta eval += 999;
                    draw tweaks black drawn = 1;
                }
                If (NUM BLACK PAWNS (EVAL) == 1)
                {
                    Call draw_tweaks.outside_pawn(64)(most advanced black pawn file (eval))(8)(((NUM BLACK PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) == 0) Or ((NUM BLACK BISHOPS (EVAL) == 1) And (BLACK BISHOP TYPE (EVAL) == "dark"))))((1 == 1));
                    Call draw_tweaks.outside_pawn(57)(most advanced black pawn file (eval))(1)(((NUM BLACK PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) == 0) Or ((NUM BLACK BISHOPS (EVAL) == 1) And (NUM BLACK BISHOPS (EVAL) == "light"))))((1 == 1));
                }
            }
            Stop(this script);
        }
    }
}

Define draw_tweaks.opposite_bishops (warp=true)
{
    If (((NUM WHITE MAJOR PIECES (EVAL) + NUM BLACK MAJOR PIECES (EVAL)) == 0) And ((NUM WHITE KNIGHTS (EVAL) + NUM BLACK KNIGHTS (EVAL)) == 0))
    {
        If ((NUM WHITE BISHOPS (EVAL) == 1) And (NUM BLACK BISHOPS (EVAL) == 1))
        {
            If (Not ((WHITE BISHOP TYPE (EVAL) == BLACK BISHOP TYPE (EVAL))))
            {
                Call // comment("opposite colored bishop endings are very drawish");
                If (abs(delta passers (poss. to win)) < 3)
                {
                    Call draw_tweaks.change_delta_eval(-275) stm relative((NUM WHITE PAWNS (EVAL) > NUM BLACK PAWNS (EVAL)));
                }
                Else
                {
                    Call draw_tweaks.change_delta_eval(-200) stm relative((NUM WHITE PAWNS (EVAL) > NUM BLACK PAWNS (EVAL)));
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

Define draw_tweaks.outside_pawn(string prom square)(string pawn file)(string pawn target file)(bool additional condition)(bool white?) (warp=true)
{
    If additional condition
    {
        If (pawn file == pawn target file)
        {
            Call draw_tweaks.king_closer_wrapper(prom square)(white?);
        }
    }
}

Define draw_tweaks.pawn_endgame(string depth) (warp=true)
{
    If (NO PAWNS PIECE MATERIAL (EVAL) > 0)
    {
        Stop(this script);
    }
    Call // comment("pawn endgame");
    If ((num black passers (eval) + num white passers (eval)) == 0)
    {
        Call // comment("if no passers, scale based on pawn count");
        draw tweaks delta eval += ((NUM WHITE PAWNS (EVAL) - NUM BLACK PAWNS (EVAL)) * 50);
    }
    If (NUM BLACK PAWNS (EVAL) == 1)
    {
        Call get rank and file from square index:(List.IndexOf(Current Board Position, -100));
        rank of black pawn (eval) = rank from square index;
        file of black pawn (eval) = file from square index;
        Call get chebyshev distance from square:(whiteKingID(eval)) to square 2:(List.IndexOf(Current Board Position, -100));
        white king to black pawn dist (eval) = distance from square to square;
        Call get chebyshev distance from square:(blackKingID(eval)) to square 2:(List.IndexOf(Current Board Position, -100));
        black king to black pawn dist (eval) = distance from square to square;
        If (rank of black pawn (eval) > WhiteKingRank (eval))
        {
            If ((white king to black pawn dist (eval) - ((depth % 2) == 0)) < (black king to black pawn dist (eval) - 1))
            {
                Call // comment("white is much closer to their pawn");
                draw tweaks win correction delta += 250;
            }
        }
    }
    If (NUM WHITE PAWNS (EVAL) == 1)
    {
        Call get rank and file from square index:(List.IndexOf(Current Board Position, 100));
        rank of white pawn (eval) = rank from square index;
        file of white pawn (eval) = file from square index;
        Call get chebyshev distance from square:(whiteKingID(eval)) to square 2:(List.IndexOf(Current Board Position, 100));
        white king to white pawn dist (eval) = distance from square to square;
        Call get chebyshev distance from square:(blackKingID(eval)) to square 2:(List.IndexOf(Current Board Position, 100));
        black king to white pawn dist (eval) = distance from square to square;
        If (rank of white pawn (eval) < BlackKingRank (eval))
        {
            If ((black king to white pawn dist (eval) - ((depth % 2) == 1)) < (white king to white pawn dist (eval) - 1))
            {
                Call // comment("black is much closer to their pawn");
                draw tweaks win correction delta += -250;
            }
        }
    }
}

Define draw_tweaks.rook_and_queen_scale_helper(string scale_val_1)(string scale_val_2)(string scale_val_3)(string scale_val_4) (warp=true)
{
    If ((NUM WHITE MAJOR PIECES (EVAL) + NUM BLACK MAJOR PIECES (EVAL)) == 2)
    {
        If ((NUM WHITE MINOR PIECES (EVAL) + NUM BLACK MINOR PIECES (EVAL)) == 0)
        {
            Call scale down eval value:(scale_val_1);
            If (delta passers (poss. to win) == 0)
            {
                Call scale down eval value:(scale_val_2);
                If ((most advanced white pawn rank (eval) < 7) And (most advanced black pawn rank (eval) > 2))
                {
                    Call scale down eval value:(scale_val_3);
                }
            }
        }
        If ((NUM WHITE MINOR PIECES (EVAL) + NUM BLACK MINOR PIECES (EVAL)) == 2)
        {
            Call scale down eval value:(scale_val_4);
        }
    }
}

Define draw_tweaks.special_rook | our pawns:(string our pawns) their pawns:(string their pawns) their most advanced pawn rank:(string their most advanced pawn rank) our king rank:(string our king rank) their king rank:(string their king rank) their most advanced pawn file:(string their most advanced pawn file) our king file:(string our king file) our most advanced pawn rank:(string our most advanced pawn rank) our passers:(string our passers) their passers:(string their passers) their king file:(string their king file)(bool white?) (warp=true)
{
    If (((our most advanced pawn rank > 6) Or ((their most advanced pawn rank < 3) And (our king rank > 1))) Or (our pawns > their pawns))
    {
        Stop(this script);
    }
    If (our pawns == their pawns)
    {
        If (our king rank > (their king rank + 2))
        {
            If (their king rank < our most advanced pawn rank)
            {
                If ((our most advanced pawn rank > 4) Or ((their king rank + 1) < our most advanced pawn rank))
                {
                    Call draw_tweaks.change_delta_eval(100) stm relative(white?);
                }
            }
        }
    }
    Call // comment("--- we are down a pawn, let's see if this positions *should* be a draw ---");
    If ((((our pawns == 0) Or ((our pawns == 1) And (our most advanced pawn rank < 6))) Or ((our pawns == their pawns) And (their pawns < 3))) And (their passers < 2))
    {
        If ((their pawns - our pawns) < 2)
        {
            If ((Not ((our king rank > their most advanced pawn rank))) Or ((their most advanced pawn rank > 2) And (our king rank < (their king rank - 2))))
            {
                If (Not ((((their most advanced pawn rank < 6) And (their king rank < their most advanced pawn rank)) And ((abs((our king file - their most advanced pawn file)) > 1) Or ((abs((our king file - their most advanced pawn file)) == 1) And ((abs((their king file - their most advanced pawn file)) == 1) And (abs((their king file - our king file)) == 2)))))))
                {
                    If ((abs((our king file - their most advanced pawn file)) < 2) Or (((their most advanced pawn file == 1) Or (their most advanced pawn file == 8)) And ((abs((our king file - their most advanced pawn file)) < 5) And (their pawns == 1))))
                    {
                        Call draw_tweaks.change_delta_eval(200) stm relative(white?);
                    }
                    Else
                    {
                        If (our king rank < (their king rank - 3))
                        {
                            Call draw_tweaks.change_delta_eval(50) stm relative(white?);
                            If (abs((our king file - their most advanced pawn file)) < 3)
                            {
                                Call draw_tweaks.change_delta_eval(100) stm relative(white?);
                            }
                        }
                        Else
                        {
                            If (our king rank < (their king rank - 1))
                            {
                                Call draw_tweaks.change_delta_eval(50) stm relative(white?);
                                If (abs((our king file - their most advanced pawn file)) < 3)
                                {
                                    Call draw_tweaks.change_delta_eval(50) stm relative(white?);
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        Else
        {
            If (their pawns == 2)
            {
                If (our king rank < their most advanced pawn rank)
                {
                    If (our king rank < their king rank)
                    {
                        Call draw_tweaks.change_delta_eval(35) stm relative(white?);
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
    If ((our pawns < 3) And (our passers == 0))
    {
        If (their passers > 0)
        {
            If ((their pawns - our pawns) > 1)
            {
                If (our most advanced pawn rank < 5)
                {
                    Call draw_tweaks.change_delta_eval(-125) stm relative(white?);
                }
            }
        }
    }
    If ((our pawns == 1) And (their passers > 1))
    {
        If (our most advanced pawn rank < 4)
        {
            Call draw_tweaks.change_delta_eval(-125) stm relative(white?);
        }
    }
}

Define eval.add flank atk black king square:(string square) (warp=true)
{
    Call get rank and file from square idx:(square) background function;
    If (num white attacks on square (eval)[square] < 3)
    {
        If (black king flank (eval)[file from square idx background] == 1)
        {
            If (rank from square idx background > 3)
            {
                flank attack black king counter (eval) += 1;
            }
        }
    }
}

Define eval.add flank atk white king square:(string square) (warp=true)
{
    Call get rank and file from square idx:(square) background function;
    If (num black attacks on square (eval)[square] < 3)
    {
        If (white king flank (eval)[file from square idx background] == 1)
        {
            If (rank from square idx background < 6)
            {
                flank attack white king counter (eval) += 1;
            }
        }
    }
}

Define eval.add_black_pawn_attacks(string square) (warp=true)
{
    If ((Current Board Position[square] + 0) > 0)
    {
        List.Add(Black Attacks (eval), square);
        List.Add(Black Attacks Source Piece (eval), -100);
    }
    List.ReplaceItem(Black Pawn Attacks Square (eval), square, (Black Pawn Attacks Square (eval)[square] + 1));
    List.ReplaceItem(num black attacks on square (eval), square, (num black attacks on square (eval)[square] + 1));
    List.ReplaceItem(Mobility Area White, square, 0);
}

Define eval.add_white_pawn_attacks(string square) (warp=true)
{
    If ((Current Board Position[square] + 0) < 0)
    {
        List.Add(White Attacks (eval), square);
        List.Add(White Attacks Source Piece (eval), 100);
    }
    List.ReplaceItem(White Pawn Attacks Square (eval), square, (White Pawn Attacks Square (eval)[square] + 1));
    List.ReplaceItem(num white attacks on square (eval), square, (num white attacks on square (eval)[square] + 1));
    List.ReplaceItem(Mobility Area Black, square, 0);
}

Define eval.bishop (warp=true)
{
    bishop color (eval) = Square Color[evaluation square idx];
    bishop on long diagonal (eval) = (1 * ((file from square index == rank from square index) Or (file from square index == (9 - rank from square index))));
    Call eval.piece pinned wrapper((mobility stop pawn color (eval) == -1));
    Call eval.piece_mob((piece is pinned res (eval) == 1))(piece is pinned delta rank (eval))(piece is pinned delta file (eval)) movement:(1)(1) settings:((1 == 1))()((mobility stop pawn color (eval) == -1))();
    Call eval.piece_mob((piece is pinned res (eval) == 1))(piece is pinned delta rank (eval))(piece is pinned delta file (eval)) movement:(-1)(1) settings:((1 == 1))()((mobility stop pawn color (eval) == -1))();
    Call eval.piece_mob((piece is pinned res (eval) == 1))(piece is pinned delta rank (eval))(piece is pinned delta file (eval)) movement:(1)(-1) settings:((1 == 1))()((mobility stop pawn color (eval) == -1))();
    Call eval.piece_mob((piece is pinned res (eval) == 1))(piece is pinned delta rank (eval))(piece is pinned delta file (eval)) movement:(-1)(-1) settings:((1 == 1))()((mobility stop pawn color (eval) == -1))();
    If (current piece (eval) == 330)
    {
        Call get chebyshev distance from square:(evaluation square idx) to square 2:(whiteKingID(eval));
        king protector eg (eval) += (-4.5 * distance from square to square);
        king protector mg (eval) += (-3 * distance from square to square);
        Call is square outpost?(evaluation square idx)((1 == 1)) (eval);
        Call eval.change with mg term:((15 * is square outpost res (eval))) eg term:((10 * is square outpost res (eval)));
        If (piece is attacker? (eval) == 0)
        {
            If (mobility check attacks their king ring (eval) > 0)
            {
                Call add piece as black king attacker with force:(25) (eval);
            }
        }
        If ((bishop on long diagonal (eval) == 1) And ((file from square index > 5) Or (file from square index < 4)))
        {
            If (bishop color (eval) == "light")
            {
                If ((Not ((Current Board Position[46] == 100))) And ((Not ((Current Board Position[37] == 100))) And ((Not ((Current Board Position[55] == 100))) Or (rank from square index > 1))))
                {
                    Call eval.change with mg term:(25) eg term:(0);
                }
            }
            Else
            {
                If ((Not ((Current Board Position[43] == 100))) And ((Not ((Current Board Position[36] == 100))) And ((Not ((Current Board Position[50] == 100))) Or (rank from square index > 1))))
                {
                    Call eval.change with mg term:(25) eg term:(0);
                }
            }
        }
        Call eval.update_mob(__Bishop Mobility Bonus[(piece mobility counter (eval) + 1)])(__Bishop Mobility Bonus End[(piece mobility counter (eval) + 1)])((1 == 1));
        If (bishop color (eval) == "light")
        {
            bishop colored pawns temp (eval) = num light pawns WHITE (eval);
        }
        Else
        {
            bishop colored pawns temp (eval) = num dark pawns WHITE (eval);
        }
        If (White Pawn Attacks Square (eval)[evaluation square idx] > 0)
        {
            bishop pawns malus temp (eval) = (-1 * (bishop colored pawns temp (eval) * num fully blocked center pawns white (eval)));
        }
        Else
        {
            bishop pawns malus temp (eval) = (-1 * (bishop colored pawns temp (eval) * (num fully blocked center pawns white (eval) + 1)));
        }
        Call eval.change with mg term:((bishop pawns malus temp (eval) * 1.5)) eg term:((bishop pawns malus temp (eval) * 3.5));
        If (evaluation square idx == 9)
        {
            If (Current Board Position[18] == -100)
            {
                evaluation res (WD) += -125;
            }
        }
        If (evaluation square idx == 16)
        {
            If (Current Board Position[23] == -100)
            {
                evaluation res (WD) += -125;
            }
        }
        Call eval.is_bishop_fianchetto(rank from square index)(file from square index)(-8)(100);
        If (is bishop fianchetto res (eval) == 1)
        {
            Call eval.change with mg term:(25) eg term:(0);
        }
        Stop(this script);
    }
    If (current piece (eval) == -330)
    {
        Call get chebyshev distance from square:(evaluation square idx) to square 2:(blackKingID(eval));
        king protector eg (eval) += (4.5 * distance from square to square);
        king protector mg (eval) += (3 * distance from square to square);
        Call is square outpost?(evaluation square idx)((0 == 1)) (eval);
        Call eval.change with mg term:((-15 * is square outpost res (eval))) eg term:((-10 * is square outpost res (eval)));
        If (piece is attacker? (eval) == 0)
        {
            If (mobility check attacks their king ring (eval) > 0)
            {
                Call add piece as white king attacker with force:(25) (eval);
            }
        }
        If ((bishop on long diagonal (eval) == 1) And ((file from square index > 5) Or (file from square index < 4)))
        {
            If (bishop color (eval) == "dark")
            {
                If ((Not ((Current Board Position[22] == -100))) And ((Not ((Current Board Position[29] == -100))) And ((Not ((Current Board Position[15] == -100))) Or (rank from square index < 8))))
                {
                    Call eval.change with mg term:(-25) eg term:(0);
                }
            }
            Else
            {
                If ((Not ((Current Board Position[19] == -100))) And ((Not ((Current Board Position[28] == -100))) And ((Not ((Current Board Position[10] == -100))) Or (rank from square index < 8))))
                {
                    Call eval.change with mg term:(-25) eg term:(0);
                }
            }
        }
        Call eval.update_mob(__Bishop Mobility Bonus[(piece mobility counter (eval) + 1)])(__Bishop Mobility Bonus End[(piece mobility counter (eval) + 1)])((0 == 1));
        If (bishop color (eval) == "light")
        {
            bishop colored pawns temp (eval) = num light pawns BLACK (eval);
        }
        Else
        {
            bishop colored pawns temp (eval) = num dark pawns BLACK (eval);
        }
        If (Black Pawn Attacks Square (eval)[evaluation square idx] > 0)
        {
            bishop pawns malus temp (eval) = (1 * (bishop colored pawns temp (eval) * num fully blocked center pawns black (eval)));
        }
        Else
        {
            bishop pawns malus temp (eval) = (1 * (bishop colored pawns temp (eval) * (num fully blocked center pawns black (eval) + 1)));
        }
        Call eval.change with mg term:((bishop pawns malus temp (eval) * 1.5)) eg term:((bishop pawns malus temp (eval) * 3.5));
        If (evaluation square idx == 49)
        {
            If (Current Board Position[42] == 100)
            {
                evaluation res (WD) += 125;
            }
        }
        If (evaluation square idx == 56)
        {
            If (Current Board Position[47] == 100)
            {
                evaluation res (WD) += 125;
            }
        }
        Call eval.is_bishop_fianchetto((9 - rank from square index))(file from square index)(8)(-100);
        If (is bishop fianchetto res (eval) == 1)
        {
            Call eval.change with mg term:(-25) eg term:(0);
        }
        Stop(this script);
    }
}

Define eval.black_king_safety (warp=true)
{
    Shelter Pawns Kingside (eval) = 0;
    Shelter Pawns Queenside (eval) = 0;
    Shelter Pawns No Castle (eval) = 0;
    Shelter Val Kingside (eval) = "none";
    Shelter Val Queenside (eval) = "none";
    Shelter Val No Castle (eval) = 0;
    Black King Shelter Val = 0;
    Black King Attacked Val = 0;
    num black shield pawns = 0;
    king can pseudo-castle (eval) = 0;
    Call get rank and file from square index:(blackKingID(eval));
    If (rank from square index < 7)
    {
        Black King Shelter Val += 100;
    }
    Black King Attacked Val += Operator.Round(((black king attacking force * Power of Attack (with # of attackers)[num black king attackers (eval)]) * 1));
    If (((Current Board Position[7] == -500) And (blackKingID(eval) == 8)) Or ((Current Board Position[2] == -500) And (blackKingID(eval) == 1)))
    {
        Black King Attacked Val += 45;
    }
    If ((BlackKingSide (eval) == "king") Or (((blackKingID(eval) == 5) And (Current Board Position[8] == -500)) And ((isEndgame? (eval) == 0) Or ((Current Board Position[6] == "") And (Current Board Position[7] == "")))))
    {
        If ((blackKingID(eval) == 5) And (Current Board Position[8] == -500))
        {
            king can pseudo-castle (eval) = 1;
        }
        If (Current Board Position[14] == -100)
        {
            Shelter Val Kingside (eval) += (PAWN SHIELD BONUS * -1);
            num black shield pawns += 1;
        }
        Else
        {
            If (Current Board Position[22] == -100)
            {
                Shelter Val Kingside (eval) += (PAWN SHIELD BONUS * -0.75);
            }
            Else
            {
                If (Current Board Position[30] == -100)
                {
                    Shelter Val Kingside (eval) += (PAWN SHIELD BONUS * -0.15);
                }
                Else
                {
                    If (abs(Most Advanced Black Pawn[6]) < 999)
                    {
                        Shelter Val Kingside (eval) += (PAWN SHIELD BONUS * -0.05);
                    }
                    Else
                    {
                        Shelter Val Kingside (eval) += (NO PAWN SHIELD PENALTY * -1);
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        If ((Current Board Position[15] == -100) Or (Current Board Position[23] == -100))
        {
            If (Current Board Position[15] == -100)
            {
                Shelter Val Kingside (eval) += (PAWN SHIELD BONUS * -1);
            }
            Else
            {
                Shelter Val Kingside (eval) += (PAWN SHIELD BONUS * -0.6);
            }
            num black shield pawns += 1;
        }
        Else
        {
            If (abs(Most Advanced Black Pawn[7]) == 999)
            {
                Shelter Val Kingside (eval) += (NO PAWN SHIELD PENALTY * -2);
            }
        }
        If (((Current Board Position[16] == -100) Or (Current Board Position[24] == -100)) And ((file from square index > 6) Or (king can pseudo-castle (eval) == 1)))
        {
            Shelter Val Kingside (eval) += (PAWN SHIELD BONUS * -1);
            num black shield pawns += 1;
        }
    }
    If ((BlackKingSide (eval) == "queen") Or (((blackKingID(eval) == 5) And (Current Board Position[1] == -500)) And (isEndgame? (eval) == 0)))
    {
        If ((blackKingID(eval) == 5) And (Current Board Position[1] == -500))
        {
            king can pseudo-castle (eval) = 1;
        }
        If (((Current Board Position[9] == -100) Or ((Current Board Position[17] == -100) Or (Current Board Position[25] == -100))) And (Not ((BlackKingRank (eval) < Least Advanced Black Pawn[1]))))
        {
            If (BlackKingFile (eval) < 3)
            {
                num black shield pawns += 1;
                If ((Current Board Position[9] == -100) Or (Current Board Position[17] == -100))
                {
                    Shelter Val Queenside (eval) += (PAWN SHIELD BONUS * -1);
                }
                Else
                {
                    Shelter Val Queenside (eval) += (PAWN SHIELD BONUS * -0.25);
                }
            }
        }
        Else
        {
            Shelter Val Queenside (eval) += (NO PAWN SHIELD PENALTY * -1.25);
        }
        If (((Current Board Position[10] == -100) Or (Current Board Position[18] == -100)) And (Not ((BlackKingRank (eval) < Least Advanced Black Pawn[2]))))
        {
            Shelter Val Queenside (eval) += (PAWN SHIELD BONUS * -1);
            num black shield pawns += 1;
        }
        Else
        {
            Shelter Val Queenside (eval) += (NO PAWN SHIELD PENALTY * -1);
            Black King Shelter Val += 25;
        }
        If (((Current Board Position[11] == -100) Or (Current Board Position[19] == -100)) And (Not ((BlackKingRank (eval) < Least Advanced Black Pawn[3]))))
        {
            If (Current Board Position[11] == -100)
            {
                Shelter Val Queenside (eval) += (PAWN SHIELD BONUS * -1);
            }
            Else
            {
                Shelter Val Queenside (eval) += (PAWN SHIELD BONUS * -0.3);
            }
            num black shield pawns += 1;
        }
        Else
        {
            Shelter Val Queenside (eval) += (NO PAWN SHIELD PENALTY * -0.5);
        }
        If (Current Board Position[17] == 330)
        {
            Shelter Val Queenside (eval) += 50;
        }
    }
    If (abs(Least Advanced Black Pawn[4]) == 999)
    {
        Shelter Val No Castle (eval) += 15;
        If (Open File? (eval)[4] == 1)
        {
            If ((blackKingID(eval) == 5) And ((Current Board Position[6] == "") And (Current Board Position[7] == "")))
            {
                Shelter Val No Castle (eval) += -5;
            }
            Else
            {
                Shelter Val No Castle (eval) += 35;
            }
        }
    }
    If (abs(Least Advanced Black Pawn[5]) == 999)
    {
        Shelter Val No Castle (eval) += 15;
        If (Open File? (eval)[5] == 1)
        {
            If ((blackKingID(eval) == 5) And ((Current Board Position[6] == "") And (Current Board Position[7] == "")))
            {
                Shelter Val No Castle (eval) += -5;
            }
            Else
            {
                Shelter Val No Castle (eval) += 35;
            }
        }
    }
    Black King Shelter Val = Shelter Val No Castle (eval);
    If ((Shelter Val Kingside (eval) < Black King Shelter Val) And (Not ((Shelter Val Kingside (eval) == "none"))))
    {
        Black King Shelter Val = Shelter Val Kingside (eval);
    }
    If ((Shelter Val Queenside (eval) < Black King Shelter Val) And (Not ((Shelter Val Queenside (eval) == "none"))))
    {
        Black King Shelter Val = Shelter Val Queenside (eval);
    }
    If (BlackKingSide (eval) == "")
    {
        If (isOpening (eval) == 0)
        {
            If ((abs(Least Advanced Black Pawn[4]) == 999) And (abs(Least Advanced Black Pawn[5]) == 999))
            {
                If (WHITE MATERIAL (NO PAWNS) > 2000)
                {
                    If (num black king attacks (eval) > 2)
                    {
                        Black King Shelter Val += 125;
                    }
                    Else
                    {
                        Black King Shelter Val += 55;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        Else
        {
            If (Not ((Current Board Position[14] == -100)))
            {
                Black King Shelter Val += 35;
            }
        }
    }
}

Define eval.change with mg term:(string mg term) eg term:(string eg term) (warp=true)
{
    change board eval tapered val = Operator.Round((((mg term * EVAL PHASE (eval)) + (eg term * (128 - EVAL PHASE (eval)))) / 128));
    evaluation res (WD) += change board eval tapered val;
}

Define eval.change_psts_stats(bool endgame?)(string value) (warp=true)
{
    If endgame?
    {
        If (current piece (eval) < 0)
        {
            Black PSTs End (eval) += value;
            Stop(this script);
        }
        White PSTs End (eval) += value;
        Stop(this script);
    }
    If (current piece (eval) < 0)
    {
        Black PSTs Middle (eval) += value;
        Stop(this script);
    }
    White PSTs Middle (eval) += value;
}

Define eval.draw_tweaks(string draw eval)(string depth) (warp=true)
{
    Call // comment("--- Possible to win: scales endgames to better reflect expected game outcome ---");
    Call draw_tweaks.init;
    Call // comment("--- Easily winning positions ---");
    Call draw_tweaks.easily_winning;
    If (possible to win finished (eval) == 1)
    {
        Stop(this script);
    }
    Call // comment("--- One side has drawn material / position ---");
    Call draw_tweaks.one_side_drawn((1 == 1))(draw eval);
    Call draw_tweaks.one_side_drawn((0 == 1))(draw eval);
    Call // comment("--- Minor or Exchange Up Endgame (Pawnless) ---");
    Call draw_tweaks.minor_or_exchange_up;
    Call // comment("--- Pawns-only endgame ---");
    Call draw_tweaks.pawn_endgame(depth);
    Call // comment("--- Major (Rook & Queen) Ending ---");
    Call draw_tweaks.majors_ending(draw eval);
    Call // comment("--- Opposite coloured bishops ending ---");
    Call draw_tweaks.opposite_bishops;
    Call // comment("--- Apply the delta eval ---");
    Call draw_tweaks.apply_delta_eval(CPU CONTEMPT VALUE);
}

Define eval.endgame_detection (warp=true)
{
    draw by material? (eval) = 0;
    isOpening (eval) = 0;
    isEndgame? (eval) = 0;
    isSimpleEndgame? (eval) = 0;
    BLACK IN ENDGAME? (EVAL) = 0;
    WHITE IN ENDGAME? (EVAL) = 0;
    If ((WHITE MATERIAL (NO PAWNS) < (ENDGAME MATERIAL THRESHOLD / 2)) Or ((NUM WHITE MAJOR PIECES (EVAL) + NUM WHITE MINOR PIECES (EVAL)) < 4))
    {
        WHITE IN ENDGAME? (EVAL) = 1;
    }
    If ((BLACK MATERIAL (NO PAWNS) < (ENDGAME MATERIAL THRESHOLD / 2)) Or ((NUM BLACK MAJOR PIECES (EVAL) + NUM BLACK MINOR PIECES (EVAL)) < 4))
    {
        BLACK IN ENDGAME? (EVAL) = 1;
    }
    If ((NUM WHITE MINOR PIECES (EVAL) + NUM BLACK MINOR PIECES (EVAL)) < 5)
    {
        If ((NUM WHITE MAJOR PIECES (EVAL) + NUM BLACK MAJOR PIECES (EVAL)) == 0)
        {
            Call // comment("simple endgame");
            isSimpleEndgame? (eval) = 1;
        }
    }
    Call // comment("--- Opening detection ---");
    If ((NO PAWNS PIECE MATERIAL (EVAL) > 5700) And ((BLACK MINOR PIECES DEVELOPED (EVAL) + WHITE MINOR PIECES DEVELOPED (EVAL)) < 6))
    {
        isOpening (eval) = 1;
    }
    Call // comment("the goal of the following checks is to see if there is a "dead" draw by material");
    Call // comment("however, endgames like KRN vs KR can be a bit tricky, so simply scale down the eval in the "possible to win" section");
    If ((NO PAWNS PIECE MATERIAL (EVAL) < ENDGAME MATERIAL THRESHOLD) Or (((NUM WHITE MAJOR PIECES (EVAL) + NUM WHITE MINOR PIECES (EVAL)) < 4) And ((NUM BLACK MAJOR PIECES (EVAL) + NUM BLACK MINOR PIECES (EVAL)) < 4)))
    {
        isEndgame? (eval) = 1;
        If (NUM TOTAL PAWNS (EVAL) == 0)
        {
            Call // comment("no pawns on board");
            If ((NUM WHITE MAJOR PIECES (EVAL) + NUM BLACK MAJOR PIECES (EVAL)) == 0)
            {
                Call // comment("no major pieces on board");
                If ((NUM BLACK MINOR PIECES (EVAL) < 2) And (NUM WHITE MINOR PIECES (EVAL) < 2))
                {
                    evaluation res (WD) = CPU CONTEMPT VALUE;
                    draw by material? (eval) = 1;
                    Stop(this script);
                }
                If ((NUM BLACK MINOR PIECES (EVAL) == 0) And ((NUM WHITE MINOR PIECES (EVAL) == 2) And (NUM WHITE KNIGHTS (EVAL) == 2)))
                {
                    evaluation res (WD) = CPU CONTEMPT VALUE;
                    draw by material? (eval) = 1;
                    Stop(this script);
                }
                If ((NUM WHITE MINOR PIECES (EVAL) == 0) And ((NUM BLACK MINOR PIECES (EVAL) == 2) And (NUM BLACK KNIGHTS (EVAL) == 2)))
                {
                    evaluation res (WD) = CPU CONTEMPT VALUE;
                    draw by material? (eval) = 1;
                    Stop(this script);
                }
            }
            Call // comment("some major pieces");
            If (((NUM WHITE MINOR PIECES (EVAL) + NUM BLACK MINOR PIECES (EVAL)) == 0) And (((NUM BLACK MAJOR PIECES (EVAL) + NUM WHITE MAJOR PIECES (EVAL)) == 2) And ((NUM BLACK ROOKS (EVAL) == 1) And (NUM WHITE ROOKS (EVAL) == 1))))
            {
                evaluation res (WD) = CPU CONTEMPT VALUE;
                draw by material? (eval) = 1;
                Stop(this script);
            }
            If (((NUM WHITE MINOR PIECES (EVAL) + NUM BLACK MINOR PIECES (EVAL)) == 0) And (((NUM BLACK MAJOR PIECES (EVAL) + NUM WHITE MAJOR PIECES (EVAL)) == 2) And ((NUM BLACK QUEENS (EVAL) == 1) And (NUM WHITE QUEENS (EVAL) == 1))))
            {
                evaluation res (WD) = CPU CONTEMPT VALUE;
                draw by material? (eval) = 1;
                Stop(this script);
            }
        }
    }
}

Define eval.full_reset (warp=true)
{
    Call reset eval function vars;
    Call clear and init eval function lists;
}

Define eval.general_eval(string depth) (warp=true)
{
    Call // comment("--- general evaluation ---");
    Call // comment("let's first loop over all pieces (excluding pawns)");
    evaluation square idx outer = 0;
    Repeat (List.Length(Squares With Pieces (Eval)))
    {
        evaluation square idx outer += 1;
        evaluation square idx = (Squares With Pieces (Eval)[evaluation square idx outer] + 0);
        current piece (eval) = Current Board Position[evaluation square idx];
        Call eval.piece_eval_inner(depth);
    }
    Call // comment("now let's loop over all pawns (as pawns often require detailed attack info)");
    evaluation square idx outer = 0;
    Repeat (List.Length(Squares with Pawns (eval)))
    {
        evaluation square idx outer += 1;
        evaluation square idx = (Squares with Pawns (eval)[evaluation square idx outer] + 0);
        current piece (eval) = Current Board Position[evaluation square idx];
        Call eval.piece_eval_inner(depth);
    }
    Call // comment("--- endgame pawn proximity ---");
    If (isEndgame? (eval) == 1)
    {
        king pawn tropism total value (eval) += (3.5 * (king pawn tropism dist to black (eval) / king pawn tropism weights (eval)));
        king pawn tropism total value (eval) += (-1 * (3.5 * (king pawn tropism dist to white (eval) / king pawn tropism weights (eval))));
        king pawn tropism total value (eval) = Operator.Round(king pawn tropism total value (eval));
        king passer proximity total (eval) = Operator.Round((king passer proximity total (eval) * 0.5));
        Call eval.change with mg term:(0) eg term:(king passer proximity total (eval));
        Call eval.change with mg term:((-10 * (WhiteKingPawnlessFlank (eval) - BlackKingPawnlessFlank (eval)))) eg term:((-47.5 * (WhiteKingPawnlessFlank (eval) - BlackKingPawnlessFlank (eval))));
    }
    Else
    {
        king passer proximity total (eval) = 0;
    }
    If (isOpening (eval) == 1)
    {
        Call eval.opening_correction(depth);
    }
    Call // comment("--- mobility ---");
    Call eval.change with mg term:(MOBILITY mg (eval)) eg term:(MOBILITY eg (eval));
    MOBILITY TOTAL TAPERED (EVAL) = change board eval tapered val;
    Call eval.get_delta_change(MOBILITY RAW WHITE mg (eval))(MOBILITY RAW WHITE eg (eval));
    MOBILITY WHITE RAW TAPERED (EVAL) = change board eval tapered val;
    Call eval.get_delta_change(MOBILITY RAW BLACK mg (eval))(MOBILITY RAW BLACK eg (eval));
    MOBILITY BLACK RAW TAPERED (EVAL) = change board eval tapered val;
    Call // comment("--- psts (piece square tables) ---");
    Call eval.change with mg term:((White PSTs Middle (eval) + Black PSTs Middle (eval))) eg term:((White PSTs End (eval) + Black PSTs End (eval)));
    Call // comment("--- king protectors ---");
    Call eval.change with mg term:(king protector mg (eval)) eg term:(king protector eg (eval));
    Call // comment("--- More threat analysis (now that we have fully completed attack tables ---");
    Call eval.change with mg term:((12 * (eval.white_king_threat_val > 0))) eg term:((45 * (eval.white_king_threat_val > 0)));
    Call eval.change with mg term:((-12 * (eval.black_king_threat_val > 0))) eg term:((-45 * (eval.black_king_threat_val > 0)));
    Call eval.weak_pieces;
    Call eval.position_threats;
    Call eval.queen_attacked_threats;
    Call eval.heavy_passer_bonus(depth);
    Call // comment("--- SPACE calcs (SF idea) ---");
    evaluation square idx = 0;
    Repeat (64)
    {
        evaluation square idx += 1;
        Call change area counter (eval);
    }
    blocked pawns total (eval) = (pawn blocked black by pawn (eval) + pawn blocked white by pawn (eval));
    Call set space with pieces:(NUM BLACK PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL)) pawns:(NUM BLACK PAWNS (EVAL))((0 == 1));
    Call set space with pieces:(NUM WHITE PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL)) pawns:(NUM WHITE PAWNS (EVAL))((1 == 1));
    If (NO PAWNS PIECE MATERIAL (EVAL) > 5000)
    {
        space total res (eval) = ((area counter white (eval) * (space weight white (eval) * space weight white (eval))) / 16);
        space total res (eval) += ((-1 * (area counter black (eval) * (space weight black (eval) * space weight black (eval)))) / 16);
        space total res (eval) = Operator.Round((space total res (eval) / 2));
        Call eval.change with mg term:(space total res (eval)) eg term:(0);
    }
    Call // comment("--- See which pieces are hanging ---");
    Call eval.get hanging states((1 == 1));
    Call eval.get hanging states((1 == 0));
    Call // comment("--- king pawn tropism ---");
    evaluation res (WD) += king pawn tropism total value (eval);
}

Define eval.get hanging states(bool white) (warp=true)
{
    hanging state idx (eval) = 0;
    If white
    {
        Repeat (List.Length(White Attacks (eval)))
        {
            hanging state idx (eval) += 1;
            hanging state our square id (eval) = White Attacks (eval)[hanging state idx (eval)];
            Call hanging state inner with their pawn attacks on square:(Black Pawn Attacks Square (eval)[hanging state our square id (eval)]) their king id:(blackKingID(eval)) their attacks on square:(num black attacks on square (eval)[hanging state our square id (eval)]) our attacks on square:(num white attacks on square (eval)[hanging state our square id (eval)]) multiplier:(1) square:(hanging state our square id (eval));
        }
    }
    Else
    {
        Repeat (List.Length(Black Attacks (eval)))
        {
            hanging state idx (eval) += 1;
            hanging state our square id (eval) = Black Attacks (eval)[hanging state idx (eval)];
            Call hanging state inner with their pawn attacks on square:(White Pawn Attacks Square (eval)[hanging state our square id (eval)]) their king id:(whiteKingID(eval)) their attacks on square:(num white attacks on square (eval)[hanging state our square id (eval)]) our attacks on square:(num black attacks on square (eval)[hanging state our square id (eval)]) multiplier:(-1) square:(hanging state our square id (eval));
        }
    }
}

Define eval.get_delta_change(string mg term)(string eg term) (warp=true)
{
    change board eval tapered val = Operator.Round((((mg term * EVAL PHASE (eval)) + (eg term * (128 - EVAL PHASE (eval)))) / 128));
}

Define eval.get_info (warp=true)
{
    Call // comment("get the general info the rest of the evaluation function will need");
    evaluation square idx = 0;
    Repeat (64)
    {
        evaluation square idx += 1;
        Call eval.get_info_inner;
    }
    ABS PAWN DIFF (EVAL) = abs((NUM WHITE PAWNS (EVAL) - NUM BLACK PAWNS (EVAL)));
    pawn file average (eval) = (pawn file average (eval) / (NUM WHITE PAWNS (EVAL) + NUM BLACK PAWNS (EVAL)));
    Call get rank and file from square index:(whiteKingID(eval));
    WhiteKingFile (eval) = file from square index;
    WhiteKingRank (eval) = rank from square index;
    Call get rank and file from square index:(blackKingID(eval));
    BlackKingFile (eval) = file from square index;
    BlackKingRank (eval) = rank from square index;
    Call eval.king_attack_areas;
    Call eval.king_on_pawnless_flank;
    Call eval.endgame_detection;
    PIECE VALUE BONUS TOTAL (EVAL) = 0;
    If (draw by material? (eval) == 1)
    {
        Stop(this script);
    }
    Call eval.get_phase;
    PIECE VALUE BONUS TOTAL (EVAL) = Operator.Round((((PIECE VALUE BONUS MIDDLEGAME (EVAL) * EVAL PHASE (eval)) + (PIECE VALUE BONUS ENDGAME (EVAL) * (128 - EVAL PHASE (eval)))) / 128));
    Call eval.position_imbalance;
    evaluation res (WD) += (PIECE VALUE BONUS TOTAL (EVAL) + IMBALANCE VALUE BONUS TOTAL (EVAL));
    Call // comment("--- piece combo ---");
    Call eval.piece_combo;
    Call // comment("--- more blocked info ---");
    Call eval.get_more_blocked_info;
}

Define eval.get_info_inner (warp=true)
{
    Call // comment("get and store the info based on the current evaluation square idx");
    List.Add(Black King Ring (eval), 0);
    List.Add(White King Ring (eval), 0);
    Call get rank and file from square index:(evaluation square idx);
    current piece (eval) = Current Board Position[evaluation square idx];
    current piece type (eval) = abs(current piece (eval));
    If (current piece type (eval) == 0)
    {
        Stop(this script);
    }
    TOTAL MATERIAL (eval) += current piece type (eval);
    Call eval.update_piece_mat;
    If (current piece (eval) == -100)
    {
        Call // comment("black pawn");
        List.Add(Squares with Pawns (eval), evaluation square idx);
        If (abs(Current Board Position[(evaluation square idx + 8)]) > 0)
        {
            If ((file from square index > 2) And (file from square index < 7))
            {
                num fully blocked center pawns black (eval) += 1;
            }
        }
        If (rank from square index < most advanced black pawn rank (eval))
        {
            most advanced black pawn rank (eval) = rank from square index;
            most advanced black pawn file (eval) = file from square index;
        }
        If ((file from square index > 1) And (file from square index < 8))
        {
            If (rank from square index < 6)
            {
                num central black pawns past 6th (eval) += 1;
                If (rank from square index < 5)
                {
                    num central black pawns past 5th (eval) += 1;
                }
            }
        }
        If (Square Color[evaluation square idx] == "light")
        {
            num light pawns BLACK (eval) += 1;
        }
        Else
        {
            num dark pawns BLACK (eval) += 1;
        }
        If (file from square index < 5)
        {
            BLACK QUEEN SIDE PAWNS (EVAL) += 1;
        }
        Else
        {
            BLACK KING SIDE PAWNS (EVAL) += 1;
        }
        List.ReplaceItem(Open File? (eval), file from square index, 0);
        If (rank from square index < Most Advanced Black Pawn[file from square index])
        {
            List.ReplaceItem(Most Advanced Black Pawn, file from square index, rank from square index);
        }
        If (rank from square index > Least Advanced Black Pawn[file from square index])
        {
            List.ReplaceItem(Least Advanced Black Pawn, file from square index, rank from square index);
        }
        If ((Current Board Position[(evaluation square idx + 8)] == 100) Or ((((Current Board Position[(evaluation square idx + 15)] == 100) And (file from square index > 1)) And ((Current Board Position[(evaluation square idx + 17)] == 100) And (file from square index < 8))) And (rank from square index > 3)))
        {
            pawn blocked black by pawn (eval) += 1;
        }
        If (Current Board Position[(evaluation square idx + 8)] == 100)
        {
            num black pawns blocked fully by their pawn (eval) += 1;
        }
        If ((rank from square index > 5) Or (abs(Current Board Position[(evaluation square idx + 8)]) > 0))
        {
            List.ReplaceItem(Mobility Area Black, evaluation square idx, 0);
        }
        If (file from square index > 1)
        {
            Call eval.add_black_pawn_attacks((evaluation square idx + 7));
        }
        If (file from square index < 8)
        {
            Call eval.add_black_pawn_attacks((evaluation square idx + 9));
        }
        pawn file average (eval) += file from square index;
        Stop(this script);
    }
    If (current piece (eval) == 100)
    {
        Call // comment("white pawn");
        List.Add(Squares with Pawns (eval), evaluation square idx);
        If (abs(Current Board Position[(evaluation square idx - 8)]) > 0)
        {
            If ((file from square index > 2) And (file from square index < 7))
            {
                num fully blocked center pawns white (eval) += 1;
            }
        }
        If (rank from square index > most advanced white pawn rank (eval))
        {
            most advanced white pawn rank (eval) = rank from square index;
            most advanced white pawn file (eval) = file from square index;
        }
        If ((file from square index > 1) And (file from square index < 8))
        {
            If (rank from square index > 3)
            {
                num central white pawns past 3rd (eval) += 1;
                If (rank from square index > 4)
                {
                    num central white pawns past 4th (eval) += 1;
                }
            }
        }
        If (Square Color[evaluation square idx] == "light")
        {
            num light pawns WHITE (eval) += 1;
        }
        Else
        {
            num dark pawns WHITE (eval) += 1;
        }
        If (file from square index < 5)
        {
            WHITE QUEEN SIDE PAWNS (EVAL) += 1;
        }
        Else
        {
            WHITE KING SIDE PAWNS (EVAL) += 1;
        }
        List.ReplaceItem(Open File? (eval), file from square index, 0);
        If (rank from square index > Most Advanced White Pawn[file from square index])
        {
            List.ReplaceItem(Most Advanced White Pawn, file from square index, rank from square index);
        }
        If (rank from square index < Least Advanced White Pawn[file from square index])
        {
            List.ReplaceItem(Least Advanced White Pawn, file from square index, rank from square index);
        }
        If ((Current Board Position[(evaluation square idx - 8)] == -100) Or ((((Current Board Position[(evaluation square idx - 17)] == -100) And (file from square index > 1)) And ((Current Board Position[(evaluation square idx - 15)] == -100) And (file from square index < 8))) And (rank from square index < 6)))
        {
            pawn blocked white by pawn (eval) += 1;
        }
        If (Current Board Position[(evaluation square idx - 8)] == -100)
        {
            num white pawns blocked fully by their pawn (eval) += 1;
        }
        If ((rank from square index < 4) Or (abs(Current Board Position[(evaluation square idx - 8)]) > 0))
        {
            List.ReplaceItem(Mobility Area White, evaluation square idx, 0);
        }
        If (file from square index < 8)
        {
            Call eval.add_white_pawn_attacks((evaluation square idx - 7));
        }
        If (file from square index > 1)
        {
            Call eval.add_white_pawn_attacks((evaluation square idx - 9));
        }
        pawn file average (eval) += file from square index;
        Stop(this script);
    }
    If (current piece (eval) == -500)
    {
        List.ReplaceItem(Black Rooks On File, file from square index, (Black Rooks On File[file from square index] + 1));
        Stop(this script);
    }
    If (current piece (eval) == 500)
    {
        List.ReplaceItem(White Rooks on File, file from square index, (White Rooks on File[file from square index] + 1));
        Stop(this script);
    }
    If (current piece (eval) == -900)
    {
        List.ReplaceItem(Mobility Area Black, evaluation square idx, 0);
        BlackQueenID (eval) = evaluation square idx;
        Stop(this script);
    }
    If (current piece (eval) == 900)
    {
        List.ReplaceItem(Mobility Area White, evaluation square idx, 0);
        WhiteQueenID(eval) = evaluation square idx;
        Stop(this script);
    }
    If ((current piece (eval) == -320) Or (current piece (eval) == -330))
    {
        Call black minor piece is developed?(evaluation square idx);
        Stop(this script);
    }
    If ((current piece (eval) == 320) Or (current piece (eval) == 330))
    {
        Call white minor piece is developed?(evaluation square idx);
    }
}

Define eval.get_more_blocked_info (warp=true)
{
    num open files (eval) = 0;
    num files without white pawns (eval) = 0;
    num files without black pawns (eval) = 0;
    num advanced white pawns at their king (eval) = 0;
    num advanced black pawns at their king (eval) = 0;
    get more blocked info idx = 0;
    Repeat (8)
    {
        get more blocked info idx += 1;
        If (Open File? (eval)[get more blocked info idx] == 1)
        {
            num open files (eval) += 1;
        }
        If (abs(Most Advanced White Pawn[get more blocked info idx]) == 999)
        {
            num files without white pawns (eval) += 1;
        }
        If (abs(Most Advanced Black Pawn[get more blocked info idx]) == 999)
        {
            num files without black pawns (eval) += 1;
        }
        If (Most Advanced White Pawn[get more blocked info idx] > 3)
        {
            If (abs((get more blocked info idx - BlackKingFile (eval))) < 2)
            {
                num advanced white pawns at their king (eval) += 1;
            }
        }
        If (Most Advanced Black Pawn[get more blocked info idx] < 4)
        {
            If (abs((get more blocked info idx - WhiteKingFile (eval))) < 2)
            {
                num advanced black pawns at their king (eval) += 1;
            }
        }
    }
}

Define eval.get_phase (warp=true)
{
    Call // comment("get the phase of the game (0 - 128), from Stockfish");
    phase endgame limit (eval) = 1500;
    If (NO PAWNS PIECE MATERIAL (EVAL) < 5800)
    {
        phase factor (eval) = NO PAWNS PIECE MATERIAL (EVAL);
    }
    Else
    {
        phase factor (eval) = 5800;
    }
    If (phase endgame limit (eval) > phase factor (eval))
    {
        phase factor (eval) = phase endgame limit (eval);
    }
    EVAL PHASE (eval) = Operator.Round((((phase factor (eval) - phase endgame limit (eval)) * 128) / (5800 - phase endgame limit (eval))));
}

Define eval.heavy_passer_bonus(string depth) (warp=true)
{
    If (List.Length(Passed Pawn Heavy Bonus Candidate EVAL) == 0)
    {
        Stop(this script);
    }
    check passed pawn heavy bonus idx = 0;
    Repeat (List.Length(Passed Pawn Heavy Bonus Candidate EVAL))
    {
        check passed pawn heavy bonus idx += 1;
        evaluation square idx = Passed Pawn Heavy Bonus Candidate EVAL[check passed pawn heavy bonus idx];
        Call get rank and file from square index:(evaluation square idx);
        If (Current Board Position[evaluation square idx] == 100)
        {
            Call // comment("white");
            If (rank from square index > ((9 - most advanced black passer rank (eval)) + ((depth % 2) == 1)))
            {
                evaluation res (WD) += 1200;
            }
        }
        Else
        {
            Call // comment("black");
            If ((9 - rank from square index) > (most advanced white passer rank (eval) + ((depth % 2) == 0)))
            {
                evaluation res (WD) += -1200;
            }
        }
    }
}

Define eval.is_bishop_fianchetto(string perspective rank)(string file)(string up delta)(string own pawn type) (warp=true)
{
    is bishop fianchetto res (eval) = 0;
    If (perspective rank < 3)
    {
        If ((file < 3) Or (file > 6))
        {
            If (Current Board Position[(evaluation square idx + up delta)] == own pawn type)
            {
                is bishop fianchetto res (eval) = 1;
            }
        }
    }
}

Define eval.is_mob_ok?(bool pinned?)(string pin d-rank)(string pin d-file)(string move d-rank)(string move d-file) (warp=true)
{
    If (Not (pinned?))
    {
        is mob dir ok? = 1;
        Stop(this script);
    }
    Call // comment("piece is pinned, let's find out which dirs it can move in");
    If ((pin d-rank == move d-rank) And (pin d-file == move d-file))
    {
        is mob dir ok? = 1;
        Stop(this script);
    }
    If (((0 - pin d-rank) == move d-rank) And ((0 - pin d-file) == move d-file))
    {
        is mob dir ok? = 1;
        Stop(this script);
    }
    is mob dir ok? = 0;
}

Define eval.is_pawn_attacker (warp=true)
{
    piece is attacker? (eval) = 0;
    Call get rank and file from square index:(evaluation square idx);
    If (current piece (eval) == 100)
    {
        Call // comment("white pawn");
        If (file from square index > 1)
        {
            If (Black King Ring (eval)[(evaluation square idx - 9)] > 0)
            {
                num black king attackers (eval) += 1;
                piece is attacker? (eval) = 1;
                Stop(this script);
            }
        }
        If (file from square index < 8)
        {
            If (Black King Ring (eval)[(evaluation square idx - 7)] > 0)
            {
                num black king attackers (eval) += 1;
                piece is attacker? (eval) = 1;
                Stop(this script);
            }
        }
        Stop(this script);
    }
    If (current piece (eval) == -100)
    {
        Call // comment("black pawn");
        If (file from square index > 1)
        {
            If (White King Ring (eval)[(evaluation square idx + 7)] > 0)
            {
                num white king attackers (eval) += 1;
                piece is attacker? (eval) = 1;
                Stop(this script);
            }
        }
        If (file from square index < 8)
        {
            If (White King Ring (eval)[(evaluation square idx + 9)] > 0)
            {
                num white king attackers (eval) += 1;
                piece is attacker? (eval) = 1;
                Stop(this script);
            }
        }
    }
}

Define eval.king_attack_areas (warp=true)
{
    king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) = blackKingID(eval);
    If (BlackKingFile (eval) > 7)
    {
        king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) += -1;
    }
    If (BlackKingFile (eval) < 2)
    {
        king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) += 1;
    }
    If (BlackKingRank (eval) > 7)
    {
        king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) += 8;
    }
    If (BlackKingRank (eval) < 2)
    {
        king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) += -8;
    }
    Call add square:(blackKingID(eval)) to king ring((0 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + -1) + -8)) to king ring((0 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + 0) + -8)) to king ring((0 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + 1) + -8)) to king ring((0 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + -1) + 0)) to king ring((0 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + 0) + 0)) to king ring((0 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + 1) + 0)) to king ring((0 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + -1) + 8)) to king ring((0 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + 0) + 8)) to king ring((0 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + 1) + 8)) to king ring((0 == 1)) (eval);
    king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) = whiteKingID(eval);
    If (WhiteKingFile (eval) > 7)
    {
        king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) += -1;
    }
    If (WhiteKingFile (eval) < 2)
    {
        king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) += 1;
    }
    If (WhiteKingRank (eval) > 7)
    {
        king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) += 8;
    }
    If (WhiteKingRank (eval) < 2)
    {
        king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) += -8;
    }
    Call add square:(whiteKingID(eval)) to king ring((1 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + -1) + -8)) to king ring((1 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + 0) + -8)) to king ring((1 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + 1) + -8)) to king ring((1 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + -1) + 0)) to king ring((1 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + 0) + 0)) to king ring((1 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + 1) + 0)) to king ring((1 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + -1) + 8)) to king ring((1 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + 0) + 8)) to king ring((1 == 1)) (eval);
    Call add square:(((king attack area gen center idx temp (eval) + 1) + 8)) to king ring((1 == 1)) (eval);
}

Define eval.king_on_pawnless_flank (warp=true)
{
    Call file has pawns?((BlackKingFile (eval) + -1)) (eval);
    BlackKingPawnlessFlank (eval) += file has pawns res (eval);
    Call file has pawns?((BlackKingFile (eval) + 0)) (eval);
    BlackKingPawnlessFlank (eval) += file has pawns res (eval);
    Call file has pawns?((BlackKingFile (eval) + 1)) (eval);
    BlackKingPawnlessFlank (eval) += file has pawns res (eval);
    If (BlackKingFile (eval) < 4)
    {
        Call file has pawns?(1) (eval);
        BlackKingPawnlessFlank (eval) += file has pawns res (eval);
    }
    Else
    {
        If (BlackKingFile (eval) < 6)
        {
            Call file has pawns?(3) (eval);
            BlackKingPawnlessFlank (eval) += file has pawns res (eval);
            Call file has pawns?(6) (eval);
            BlackKingPawnlessFlank (eval) += file has pawns res (eval);
        }
        Else
        {
            Call file has pawns?(8) (eval);
            BlackKingPawnlessFlank (eval) += file has pawns res (eval);
        }
    }
    If (BlackKingPawnlessFlank (eval) > 0)
    {
        BlackKingPawnlessFlank (eval) = 0;
    }
    Else
    {
        BlackKingPawnlessFlank (eval) = 1;
    }
    Call file has pawns?((WhiteKingFile (eval) + -1)) (eval);
    WhiteKingPawnlessFlank (eval) += file has pawns res (eval);
    Call file has pawns?((WhiteKingFile (eval) + 0)) (eval);
    WhiteKingPawnlessFlank (eval) += file has pawns res (eval);
    Call file has pawns?((WhiteKingFile (eval) + 1)) (eval);
    WhiteKingPawnlessFlank (eval) += file has pawns res (eval);
    If (WhiteKingFile (eval) < 4)
    {
        Call file has pawns?(1) (eval);
        WhiteKingPawnlessFlank (eval) += file has pawns res (eval);
    }
    Else
    {
        If (WhiteKingFile (eval) < 6)
        {
            Call file has pawns?(3) (eval);
            WhiteKingPawnlessFlank (eval) += file has pawns res (eval);
            Call file has pawns?(6) (eval);
            WhiteKingPawnlessFlank (eval) += file has pawns res (eval);
        }
        Else
        {
            Call file has pawns?(8) (eval);
            WhiteKingPawnlessFlank (eval) += file has pawns res (eval);
        }
    }
    If (WhiteKingPawnlessFlank (eval) > 0)
    {
        WhiteKingPawnlessFlank (eval) = 0;
    }
    Else
    {
        WhiteKingPawnlessFlank (eval) = 1;
    }
}

Define eval.king_passer_prox (warp=true)
{
    If (isPawnPassed? (eval) == 0)
    {
        Stop(this script);
    }
    If (current piece (eval) == 100)
    {
        Call // comment("white");
        If (rank from square index < 4)
        {
            Stop(this script);
        }
        pawn weight (king passer prox) = (((rank from square index - 1) * 5) - 13);
        If (pawn weight (king passer prox) < 0)
        {
            Stop(this script);
        }
        Call // comment("calculate distance to their king");
        Call get chebyshev distance from square:((evaluation square idx - 8)) to square 2:(blackKingID(eval));
        distance to king them (king passer proximity) = distance from square to square;
        If (distance to king us (king passer proximity) > 5)
        {
            distance to king us (king passer proximity) = 5;
        }
        king passer proximity total (eval) += (floor((distance to king them (king passer proximity) * (19 / 4))) * pawn weight (king passer prox));
        Call // comment("calculate distance to our king");
        Call get chebyshev distance from square:((evaluation square idx - 8)) to square 2:(whiteKingID(eval));
        distance to king us (king passer proximity) = distance from square to square;
        If (distance to king us (king passer proximity) > 5)
        {
            distance to king us (king passer proximity) = 5;
        }
        king passer proximity total (eval) += (0 - ((distance to king us (king passer proximity) * 2) * pawn weight (king passer prox)));
        If (rank from square index < 7)
        {
            Call get chebyshev distance from square:((evaluation square idx - 16)) to square 2:(whiteKingID(eval));
            distance to king us (king passer proximity) = distance from square to square;
            If (distance to king us (king passer proximity) > 5)
            {
                distance to king us (king passer proximity) = 5;
            }
            king passer proximity total (eval) += (0 - (distance to king us (king passer proximity) * pawn weight (king passer prox)));
        }
        Stop(this script);
    }
    Call // comment("black");
    If (rank from square index > 5)
    {
        Stop(this script);
    }
    pawn weight (king passer prox) = (0 - ((((9 - rank from square index) - 1) * 5) - 13));
    If (pawn weight (king passer prox) > 0)
    {
        Call // comment("flipped perspective");
        Stop(this script);
    }
    Call // comment("calculate distance to their king");
    Call get chebyshev distance from square:((evaluation square idx + 8)) to square 2:(whiteKingID(eval));
    distance to king them (king passer proximity) = distance from square to square;
    If (distance to king them (king passer proximity) > 5)
    {
        distance to king them (king passer proximity) = 5;
    }
    king passer proximity total (eval) += (floor((distance to king them (king passer proximity) * (19 / 4))) * pawn weight (king passer prox));
    Call // comment("calculate distance to our king");
    Call get chebyshev distance from square:((evaluation square idx + 8)) to square 2:(blackKingID(eval));
    distance to king us (king passer proximity) = distance from square to square;
    If (distance to king us (king passer proximity) > 5)
    {
        distance to king us (king passer proximity) = 5;
    }
    king passer proximity total (eval) += (0 - ((distance to king us (king passer proximity) * 2) * pawn weight (king passer prox)));
    If (rank from square index > 2)
    {
        Call get chebyshev distance from square:((evaluation square idx + 16)) to square 2:(blackKingID(eval));
        distance to king us (king passer proximity) = distance from square to square;
        If (distance to king us (king passer proximity) > 5)
        {
            distance to king us (king passer proximity) = 5;
        }
        king passer proximity total (eval) += (0 - (distance to king us (king passer proximity) * pawn weight (king passer prox)));
    }
}

Define eval.king_safety(bool log debug?)(string depth) (warp=true)
{
    Call eval.king_safety_opening_correction;
    Call // comment("BLACK KING SAFETY EVALUATION");
    Call eval.black_king_safety;
    Call get num safe checks for perspective((1 == 1)) (eval);
    If ((NUM WHITE QUEENS (EVAL) == 0) Or ((((num black king attackers (eval) < 2) And (Black King Shelter Val < -25)) Or (NUM WHITE PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) < 2)) And ((isEndgame? (eval) == 1) And (WHITE MATERIAL (NO PAWNS) < 1350))))
    {
        Black King Attacked Val += -100;
    }
    Call get safe check bonus with num safe checks:(num safe checks res (eval))(num safe checks extra bonus res (eval))(((depth % 2) == 0))((-1 * Black King Shelter Val))(num black king knight defenders (eval));
    Black King Attacked Val += (0.75 * safe check bonus res (eval));
    Call get weak king ring((0 == 1));
    If (num black king attackers (eval) > 1)
    {
        Black King Attacked Val += (25 * num weak king ring squares);
    }
    Black King Attacked Val += ((1 * (15 + (10 * (num weak king ring squares > 0)))) * unsafe checks total white (eval));
    Black King Attacked Val += (MOBILITY TOTAL TAPERED (EVAL) / 12);
    Black King Attacked Val += (0.35 * (((3 * flank attack white king counter (eval)) * flank attack white king counter (eval)) / 8));
    Black King Attacked Val += (-25 * num black king knight defenders (eval));
    Black King Attacked Val += (7.5 * num black king attacks (eval));
    If ((Black King Attacked Val < 25) Or (NUM WHITE PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) < 2))
    {
        Black King Attacked Val = 0;
    }
    If (WHITE MATERIAL (NO PAWNS) > 1200)
    {
        Call eval.change with mg term:(Black King Shelter Val) eg term:(0);
    }
    If (((Black King Attacked Val > 150) And (WHITE MATERIAL (NO PAWNS) > 1100)) And (num black king attackers (eval) > 1))
    {
        Call // comment("if black's king is in danger, make safe checks worth even more");
        Black King Attacked Val += (0.5 * safe check bonus res (eval));
    }
    If ((isOpening (eval) == 1) And (num black king attackers (eval) < 3))
    {
        Black King Attacked Val = (0.25 * Black King Attacked Val);
    }
    Call eval.change with mg term:(Black King Attacked Val) eg term:(((Black King Attacked Val / 10) + (100 * ((Black King Attacked Val > 250) And ((num black king attackers (eval) > 1) And ((NUM WHITE QUEENS (EVAL) > 0) Or ((num black king attackers (eval) > 2) And (NUM WHITE PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) > 2))))))));
    Call eval.change with mg term:((2 * (flank attack black king counter (eval) - flank attack white king counter (eval)))) eg term:(0);
    Call WD.log_eval(10)("b")(log debug?)();
    Call // comment("WHITE KING SAFETY EVALUATION");
    Call eval.white_king_safety;
    Call get num safe checks for perspective((0 == 1)) (eval);
    If ((NUM BLACK QUEENS (EVAL) == 0) Or ((((num white king attackers (eval) < 2) And (White King Shelter Val > 25)) Or (NUM BLACK PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) < 2)) And ((isEndgame? (eval) == 1) And (BLACK MATERIAL (NO PAWNS) < 1350))))
    {
        White King Attacked Val += 100;
    }
    Call get safe check bonus with num safe checks:(num safe checks res (eval))(num safe checks extra bonus res (eval))(((depth % 2) == 1))(White King Shelter Val)(num white king knight defenders (eval));
    White King Attacked Val += (-0.75 * safe check bonus res (eval));
    Call get weak king ring((1 == 1));
    If (num white king attackers (eval) > 1)
    {
        White King Attacked Val += (-25 * num weak king ring squares);
    }
    White King Attacked Val += ((-1 * (15 + (10 * (num weak king ring squares > 0)))) * unsafe checks total black (eval));
    White King Attacked Val += (MOBILITY TOTAL TAPERED (EVAL) / 12);
    White King Attacked Val += (-0.35 * (((3 * flank attack black king counter (eval)) * flank attack black king counter (eval)) / 8));
    White King Attacked Val += (25 * num white king knight defenders (eval));
    White King Attacked Val += (-7.5 * num white king attacks (eval));
    If ((White King Attacked Val > -25) Or (NUM BLACK PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) < 2))
    {
        White King Attacked Val = 0;
    }
    If (BLACK MATERIAL (NO PAWNS) > 1200)
    {
        Call eval.change with mg term:(White King Shelter Val) eg term:(0);
    }
    If (((White King Attacked Val < -150) And (BLACK MATERIAL (NO PAWNS) > 1100)) And (num white king attackers (eval) > 1))
    {
        Call // comment("if whites's king is in danger, make safe checks worth even more");
        White King Attacked Val += (-0.5 * safe check bonus res (eval));
    }
    If ((isOpening (eval) == 1) And (num white king attackers (eval) < 3))
    {
        White King Attacked Val = (0.25 * White King Attacked Val);
    }
    Call eval.change with mg term:(White King Attacked Val) eg term:(((White King Attacked Val / 10) - (100 * ((White King Attacked Val < -250) And ((num white king attackers (eval) > 1) And ((NUM BLACK QUEENS (EVAL) > 0) Or ((num white king attackers (eval) > 2) And (NUM BLACK PIECES (NOT PAWNS) (EVAL) > 2))))))));
    Call eval.change with mg term:((2 * (flank attack black king counter (eval) - flank attack white king counter (eval)))) eg term:(0);
    Call WD.round_eval;
    If log debug?
    {
        List.ReplaceItem(EVAL DEBUG LIST, 10, Operator.Join(Operator.Join(EVAL DEBUG LIST[10], " | "), Operator.Join(evaluation res (WD), " w")));
    }
    Call blockages (evaluation);
    Call WD.round_eval;
    If log debug?
    {
        List.ReplaceItem(EVAL DEBUG LIST, 10, Operator.Join(Operator.Join(EVAL DEBUG LIST[10], " | "), Operator.Join(evaluation res (WD), " Total")));
    }
}

Define eval.king_safety_opening_correction (warp=true)
{
    Call // comment("let's correct some king safety stuff as often the opening king safety differs profoundly from middlegame");
    If (isOpening (eval) == 1)
    {
        flank attack black king counter (eval) = (flank attack black king counter (eval) / 2);
        flank attack white king counter (eval) = (flank attack white king counter (eval) / 2);
    }
}

Define eval.knight (warp=true)
{
    knight reachable outposts (eval) = 0;
    knight attacks their king ring (eval) = 0;
    knight is king defender (eval) = 0;
    Call eval.piece pinned wrapper((mobility stop pawn color (eval) == -1));
    If (piece is pinned res (eval) == 0)
    {
        Call eval.knight mobility with delta rank:(2) delta file:(1) white perspective?:((mobility stop pawn color (eval) == -1));
        piece mobility counter (eval) += mobility in direction res;
        Call eval.knight mobility with delta rank:(2) delta file:(-1) white perspective?:((mobility stop pawn color (eval) == -1));
        piece mobility counter (eval) += mobility in direction res;
        Call eval.knight mobility with delta rank:(-2) delta file:(1) white perspective?:((mobility stop pawn color (eval) == -1));
        piece mobility counter (eval) += mobility in direction res;
        Call eval.knight mobility with delta rank:(-2) delta file:(-1) white perspective?:((mobility stop pawn color (eval) == -1));
        piece mobility counter (eval) += mobility in direction res;
        Call eval.knight mobility with delta rank:(1) delta file:(2) white perspective?:((mobility stop pawn color (eval) == -1));
        piece mobility counter (eval) += mobility in direction res;
        Call eval.knight mobility with delta rank:(1) delta file:(-2) white perspective?:((mobility stop pawn color (eval) == -1));
        piece mobility counter (eval) += mobility in direction res;
        Call eval.knight mobility with delta rank:(-1) delta file:(2) white perspective?:((mobility stop pawn color (eval) == -1));
        piece mobility counter (eval) += mobility in direction res;
        Call eval.knight mobility with delta rank:(-1) delta file:(-2) white perspective?:((mobility stop pawn color (eval) == -1));
        piece mobility counter (eval) += mobility in direction res;
    }
    If (current piece (eval) == 320)
    {
        Call get chebyshev distance from square:(evaluation square idx) to square 2:(whiteKingID(eval));
        king protector eg (eval) += (-4.5 * distance from square to square);
        king protector mg (eval) += (-4 * distance from square to square);
        Call is square outpost?(evaluation square idx)((1 == 1)) (eval);
        Call eval.change with mg term:((26 * (is square outpost res (eval) + (knight reachable outposts (eval) * 0.5)))) eg term:((18 * (is square outpost res (eval) + (knight reachable outposts (eval) * 0.5))));
        If (knight attacks their king ring (eval) > 0)
        {
            Call add piece as black king attacker with force:(35) (eval);
        }
        Call eval.update_mob(__Knight Mobility Bonus[(piece mobility counter (eval) + 1)])(__Knight Mobility Bonus End[(piece mobility counter (eval) + 1)])((1 == 1));
        If (evaluation square idx == 43)
        {
            If (Current Board Position[51] == 100)
            {
                If (Current Board Position[42] == 100)
                {
                    Call eval.change with mg term:(-15) eg term:(0);
                }
                If (Current Board Position[36] == 100)
                {
                    If (Current Board Position[28] == -100)
                    {
                        If (Not ((Current Board Position[37] == 100)))
                        {
                            Call eval.change with mg term:(-15) eg term:(-5);
                        }
